Holidays are not free everywhere.
In Hungary, holidays are precisely defined by law, and it has become a common practice that work days are moved around the holidays, which awaits us less often next year.
In the European Union and in the United States, the holidays are not uniform.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between national and state holidays and working days of rest.
The days of work rest are usually linked to church holidays or to important historical events.
We also celebrate the New Year: the last day of the old and the first day of the new year is free to work - for the New Year already so that people can rest after New Year's Eve.
There are a total of 11 free holidays throughout the year.
March 15 is a national holiday commemorating the revolution of 1848 and October 23, the commemoration of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20th we celebrate the founding of the state, on May 1st we work, on November 1st and 2nd we remember the deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, there are two-day Easter, Summer and Christmas holidays here.
Since our state, national, or religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, it has become the practice of moving the working day in cases where we work only one day before or after the holiday.
However, the price for extended weekends is that we stay at the workplace and at school on previous Saturdays.
When the day that immediately precedes or follows the holiday, we work out, it has for many years been regulated by the Minister of Labour in a special decree.
The legislation applies equally to all employers and the employees employed by them, to public servants and to persons in the public service.
However, it does not apply to companies and institutions that are in operation without interruption or operate even on working days of rest due to their destination.
This year, there will be a change in the working schedule only around the holidays at the end of the year: from December 24, life in the country will almost stop, because according to previous experience, most people "work" or use the saved time in advance between Christmas and New Year.
Next year, several of our holidays fall in the middle, respectively, for the end of the week, so the shifts of the working day will be less than this year.
For the first time, the calendar is transformed around the holiday of work, so that workers can stay at home for four days of taste.
Saturday 26 April will be a working day so that Friday 2 May can be a day of rest.
Another move relates to the holiday of October 23: on Saturday, October 18 will be working instead of Friday 24.
