What kind of insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance that protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a significant expense, which depends on various factors such as age, condition, sex, length of possession of the driver's license, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insurer.
This commitment takes the form of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the insurer will receive the agreed amount of insurance in a certain amount for taking responsibility for the payment of damages in the event of an insurance event.
Insurance is the price of insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors such as age, condition, sex, length of possession of a driver's license, the type of vehicle that is insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies determine their prices based on statistics, so the more likely it is that an accident will occur, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower insurance rates, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their precautionary nature.
In the same way, on the basis of checks, insurance companies have concluded that people living in marriage have fewer accidents than free drivers.
The way in which the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of driving, and thus the likelihood that it will have an accident.
As the frequency of driving increases, the probability increases.
There are many variables that insurers consider when determining the price of insurance.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that best corresponds to his insurer profile.
Here we will show you the most important variables for the choice of this or that type of insurance, which, in addition to meeting the type of insurer, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five face a variety of disadvantages such as little driving experience and short driving licenses when they want to negotiate insurance at an affordable price.
While insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks with an insurance discount in order to obtain insurance coverage for all risks, but at a more acceptable price.
This type of contract would entail the client’s participation in the payment of the insurance event.
“The part of the reimbursement of the insurance event provided by the client will be pre-determined in determining the price of the insurance, which will be higher, the lower the participation would be,” explains Luis Noguera, Head of First Europe in Spain, an internet intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants of the operation so that the client is insured against damage caused to other people, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Recommendations.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as it will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce insurance in the future.
The bonus is the reduction of the basic rate that an insurance company has.
On the other hand, small is the increase of the mentioned basic rate.
"Bonus and minor will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus," explains Noguera.
After crossing the twenty-five-year limit, it makes it easier for drivers to negotiate insurance, as the customer’s risk index decreases, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to arrange insurance against all risks with a discount.
"Young people usually can't take advantage of the pre-experienced experience at the time of an accident, or even when driving," says the director of a European company in Spain, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of the accident.
However, if the client is married but has no children yet, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if, of course, his economic situation allows.
Families with children are considered to be the clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a discount of insurance (which could be 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other operators, starting in the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
“Their handling is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford to get the highest discount,” said Luis Noguera.
Retirement insurance is recommended against all risks with a discount of insurance (which amounts to 150 euros) or insurance extended to other participants of the operation, if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would best suit us given our personal situation.
